BULLETIN - EAS ACTIVATION REQUESTED
CHILD ABDUCTION EMERGENCY
TEXAS DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY
RELAYED BY NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE AUSTIN/SAN ANTONIO TX
226 PM CDT THU JUL 1 2021

THE FOLLOWING MESSAGE IS TRANSMITTED AT THE REQUEST OF THE TEXAS
DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY.

THIS IS A CHILD ABDUCTION ALERT ISSUED BY THE TEXAS AMBER ALERT
NETWORK. 

THE ENNIS POLICE DEPARTMENT IS SEARCHING FOR MIGUEL DAVID LEE
RAMIREZ, WHITE, MALE, 7 MONTHS OLD, 26 INCHES, 25 POUNDS, LIGHT BROWN
HAIR, BLUE EYES, AND WEARING A WHITE MICKEY MOUSE DIAPER. 

POLICE ARE LOOKING FOR FAITH REID, WHITE, FEMALE, 20 YEARS OLD, 5
FEET 2 INCHES, 115 POUNDS, BLONDE HAIR, GREEN EYES AND UNKNOWN
CLOTHING, IN CONNECTION WITH HIS ABDUCTION.

THE SUSPECT IS DRIVING A WHITE FORD EXTENDED CAB WITH AN UNKNOWN
TEXAS PLATES.

THE SUSPECT WAS LAST HEARD FROM IN ENNIS, TEXAS.

LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICIALS BELIEVE THIS CHILD TO BE IN GRAVE OR
IMMEDIATE DANGER.  

IF YOU HAVE ANY INFORMATION REGARDING THIS ABDUCTION, CALL THE ENNIS
POLICE DEPARTMENT AT 9 7 2 8 7 5 4 4 6 2.

NEWS MEDIA POINT OF CONTACT IS ENNIS POLICE DEPARTMENT 9 7 2 8 7 5 4
4 6 2.

$$
